  "notes": [
    "This paper introduces a novel computational method called genetic Minimal Intervention Sets (gMIS) that extends beyond traditional synthetic lethality approaches by incorporating both gene knockouts and knock-ins.",
    "The method identifies various types of lethal genetic interactions including synthetic dosage lethality and tumor suppressor gene complexes.",
    "EZH2 is identified as a potential therapeutic target in hematological malignancies through specific genetic interactions with JUN and RELA.",
    "The approach demonstrates improved sensitivity in predicting essential genes compared to knockout-only methods."
  ]
